## Anti-Patterns

❌ **DON'T**: Mix DDL and DML
```sql
-- ❌ BAD
ALTER TABLE Credential ADD COLUMN new_field STRING(100);
INSERT INTO Credential (credential_id, new_field) VALUES ('id', 'value');
```

❌ **DON'T**: Modify tables without dropping property graph first
```sql
-- ❌ BAD
ALTER TABLE Credential ADD COLUMN new_field STRING(100);
-- Property graph will fail - table structure changed
```

❌ **DON'T**: Use DML to populate generated columns
```sql
-- ❌ BAD: Generated columns populate automatically
ALTER TABLE Credential ADD COLUMN a_display_name STRING(MAX) AS (normalized_name) STORED;
UPDATE Credential SET a_display_name = normalized_name;  -- Unnecessary!
```

❌ **DON'T**: Create migrations with multiple unrelated changes
```sql
-- ❌ BAD: Migration does three different things
-- Create separate migrations
```

❌ **DON'T**: Edit applied migrations
```sql
-- ❌ BAD: Once migration is applied, don't edit it
-- Create a new migration instead
```

❌ **DON'T**: Use `IF EXISTS` with DROP COLUMN
```sql
-- ❌ BAD: Causes syntax error in Spanner
ALTER TABLE Intent DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS query;

-- ✅ GOOD: Correct syntax
ALTER TABLE Intent DROP COLUMN query;
```

❌ **DON'T**: Omit parentheses in DEFAULT values
```sql
-- ❌ BAD: Missing parentheses
version INT64 NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,

-- ✅ GOOD: Include parentheses
version INT64 NOT NULL DEFAULT (1),
```

❌ **DON'T**: Use any boolean predicate in filtered index WHERE
```sql
-- ❌ BAD: IS FALSE not supported
WHERE is_deleted IS FALSE

-- ❌ BAD: IS NOT TRUE not supported
WHERE is_deleted IS NOT TRUE

-- ❌ BAD: Equality not supported
WHERE is_deleted = false

-- ✅ GOOD: Use composite index instead
CREATE INDEX idx_name ON Table(col1, is_deleted);
```

❌ **DON'T**: Use execute-sql for DDL operations
```bash
# ❌ BAD: execute-sql is for queries only
gcloud spanner databases execute-sql db --sql="DROP TABLE T"

# ✅ GOOD: Use ddl update for DDL
gcloud spanner databases ddl update db --ddl="DROP TABLE T"
```

