## Checklist

Before creating a migration, verify:

- [ ] Migration uses **DDL only** (no INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE)
- [ ] Migration file follows naming convention (`<version>_<description>.sql`)
- [ ] Migration includes proper header comment block
- [ ] Migration represents one logical change
- [ ] Property graph is dropped before table alterations (if applicable)
- [ ] Property graph is recreated after table alterations (if applicable)
- [ ] Generated columns use `AS (expression) STORED` syntax
- [ ] `IF EXISTS` used only where supported (DROP TABLE, DROP INDEX, DROP PROPERTY GRAPH)
- [ ] `IF EXISTS` NOT used with DROP COLUMN (causes syntax error)
- [ ] Indexes have descriptive names with `idx_` prefix
- [ ] Data migration is handled separately (not in migration file)
- [ ] Migration tested on development database first
- [ ] DEFAULT values use parentheses: `DEFAULT (1)` not `DEFAULT 1`
- [ ] Interleaved tables have comma before INTERLEAVE: `), INTERLEAVE IN PARENT`
- [ ] Filtered indexes only use `IS NULL`/`IS NOT NULL` (no boolean predicates)
- [ ] No string equality in filtered index WHERE clauses

---

**Remember**: Migrations are structural changes only. Data changes are handled separately via application scripts.
